issues.title: cannot import name secret
issues.body:
Description: Cannot start application.

Steps to reproduce:

``` bash
$ git clone git+ssh://git@github.com/rafallo/p2c.git
$ cd p2c
$ PYTHONPATH='.' python3.3 gui/desktop/main.py
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "gui/desktop/main.py", line 6, in <module>
    from p2c.app import P2CDaemon
  File "/home/sakar/temp/p2c/p2c/app.py", line 5, in <module>
    from catalogs.services.kickass import KickAssService
  File "/home/sakar/temp/p2c/catalogs/services/kickass.py", line 6, in <module>
    from catalogs.services.base import  BaseService
  File "/home/sakar/temp/p2c/catalogs/services/base.py", line 3, in <module>
    from .abstractbase import AbstractService
  File "/home/sakar/temp/p2c/catalogs/services/abstractbase.py", line 2, in <module>
    from p2c.ui import CategoryInfo
  File "/home/sakar/temp/p2c/p2c/ui.py", line 2, in <module>
    from catalogs.info_clients.tmdbclient import TMDBApiClient
  File "/home/sakar/temp/p2c/catalogs/info_clients/tmdbclient.py", line 5, in <module>
    from catalogs import secret
ImportError: cannot import name secret
```
